That is compact and enough for retrieval evaluation.

Status output example

When reference is found:

[HIT] config=config.search id=144 rank=2 reference='doc_abc.pdf' corrected_query='vertrag laufzeit kündigung'

When not found:

[MISS] config=config.search id=145 reference='doc_xyz.pdf' corrected_query='rechnung zahlungsziel'

Resume behavior

It resumes automatically.

Because of this primary key:

(config_name, question_id)


and this check:

if already_done(conn, config_name, question_id):
    skipped += 1
    continue

So if the run stops at question 2317, start it again and it will continue with the remaining rows.

Useful SQL queries

Hit rate per config:

SELECT
    config_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total,
    SUM(hit) AS hits,
    ROUND(100.0 * SUM(hit) / COUNT(*), 2) AS hit_rate_percent
FROM retrieval_eval
GROUP BY config_name
ORDER BY config_name;

Top-1 / Top-3 / Top-5:

SELECT
    config_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total,
    SUM(CASE WHEN rank_pos = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS top1,
    SUM(CASE WHEN rank_pos BETWEEN 1 AND 3 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS top3,
    SUM(CASE WHEN rank_pos BETWEEN 1 AND 5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS top5
FROM retrieval_eval
GROUP BY config_name
ORDER BY config_name;

Rows where reference was found:

SELECT question_id, frage, reference, corrected_query, rank_pos
FROM retrieval_eval
WHERE hit = 1
ORDER BY config_name, question_id;

